Template: capsid-server/admin_password
Type: password
Description: New password for the CaPSID "administrator" user:
 While not mandatory, it is highly recommended that you set a password
 for the CaPSID "administrator" user.
 .
 If this field is left blank, the password will not be changed.

Template: capsid-server/admin_password_again
Type: password
Description: Repeat password for the CaPSID "administrator" user:

Template: capsid-server/database_host
Default: localhost
Type: string
Description: The database server address:
 The domain name or IP address for the MongoDB database server is 
 needed to make a connection to the database. 

Template: capsid-server/database_port
Default: 27017
Type: string
Description: The database server port:
 The port for the MongoDB database server is needed
 to make a connection to the database. 

Template: capsid-server/database_name
Default: capsid
Type: string
Description: The name of the database:
 There may be several databases on this database server. 
 The name is needed to locate the database containing the 
 informatiom needed by CaPSID.

Template: capsid-server/database_username
Type: string
Description: The database server user name:
 If the database server requires authentication, a user
 name and a password will be needed to connect to the
 server. Leave this empty to skip authentication. 

Template: capsid-server/database_password
Type: password
Description: The database server password:
 If the database server requires authentication, a user
 name and a password will be needed to connect to the
 server. Leave this empty to skip authentication. 
